Daily menu of an obese child: no breakfast and dinner sausages
More than a third of children between the ages of 9 and 13 have problems with overweight, with overweight affecting 9% of the school population and obesity affecting 5%.
Obese children mostly come from families with an unhealthy lifestyle, according to current research.
It again demonstrates the importance of the environment where you grow for a healthy development of the person, as well as the models that serve as a reference.
At the table, obsessed children are fed, for example, sausages at least twice as often as children in families with normal weight.
For dinner, more than 19% of the obese had eaten chips the day before the analysis, which is linked to the prevention program “Obesity is not a coincidence.”
In families of overweight children there is no habit of playing sports, which is applicable to most current families, where only 15% of children answered that their parents, at least once a week, find time for physical exercise.
Survey of 900 children
The survey was carried out at the end of last school year and almost 900 children of Basic Education from all over the Czech Republic participated in it.
It was already the second edition of the program "Obesity is not a coincidence", which supports the General Health Insurance Company and the company Unilever.
So far, more than 12,000 children have participated in the project from the 4th to the 8th year.
A proper diet and enough family exercise are determinants, which make the number of overweight and even obese children significantly decrease.
“Only half of the children surveyed have responded that they have five diet-based meals a day: breakfast, lunch, lunch, lunch, snack and dinner, which is one of the basic conditions for a healthy diet.”
No breakfast but with built-in for dinner
Specialists warn that, in a healthy development, details are also important, which also count, such as having a set time for family breakfast.
In the Czech Republic, however, only 23% of schoolchildren have breakfast at the same time.
In most families, everyone eats breakfast alone.
But the worst thing was to find out that in 10% of households nothing is eaten.
Breakfast is, however, the basis of a correct daily diet.
The study shows that families of obese children consume insane French fries much more often.
Almost everyone - regardless of weight - drinks sweet soft drinks daily (70%).
As a rule, more than 40% of the children surveyed do sports, however, among their parents this result is reduced to less than half, only 15%.
Make your diet
The next phase of the study allowed the chosen boys (204 boys and 172 girls from 13 schools) to create their own diets from all possible offers according to their tastes and opinions.
"The dietary preferences of Czech children between the ages of 12 and 15, from the point of view of healthy eating, are far from ideal."
Among his favorite foods are pasta, meat and sweets
"The popularity of sweet sodas is especially alarming," the study's final report warns.
The main food is the palm pasta and closely followed by the poultry meat.
Practically, children always reject legumes and the taste for fish and vegetables is very low.
Changing to Healthy Habits
At the same time, the study shows that children are willing to change their eating habits if they receive the right information.
"In the control group of study participants, who filled out the questionnaire after completing the prevention program "Obesity is not a coincidence", there was in many cases a significant change in favor of the principles of healthy eating," the study results note.
It draws attention, for example, to sweet soda, where many children would start to prefer normal and running water.
Children would also more often choose poultry meat and fish for the main meal and restrict the consumption of sweet food and flour derivatives.
