Looking for alternatives in cities
Ecologists attribute the problems of cities to the migration of the field of certain protected grades; chemical applications in agriculture visibly end traditional living spaces.
Hunting, growing buildings and falling trees that house them make it difficult for birds to live.
The grasses are protected.
There are large colonies with more than 600 breeding pairs in Soest, Westphalia, among others, in the northwest, among others in Jever, Diepholz and Achim in Bremen, as well as in Leer.
