The new environmental review ordered by the State Department is likely to set aside any decision until 2013, after next year’s elections, although officials denied that the policy was involved in the decision.
Obama, in a written statement last week, described the decision as a request from the State Department, and expressed his full support.
The 1,700-kilometre pipeline would extend from Canada to the Gulf of Mexico.
It would carry 700,000 barrels a day from the province of Alberta to refineries in Texas.
For this, it would be necessary to cross six states.
It is hated by environmentalists, but loved by the working groups, who have bet on the estimated 20,000 jobs linked to the pipeline.
