The Secretariat of Communications and Transport (SCT) reported that the results cast on the accident where the Secretary of the Government, Francisco Blake Mora, and seven other people died, indicate that the helicopter was impacted directly on the ground in complete structural integrity, without the pilot being able to attempt a forced landing.
