At the press conference, the owner of the SCT, Pérez J<0xC3><0xA1>come, listed six relevant elements in the investigation:
Visual flight:
According to aeronautical regulations, the flight was performed under visual flight rules, this implies that the crew must have visibility during flight and on the ground.
Weather conditions: -
Reports in the AICM located suitable conditions for takeoff, as the aircraft advances to the border area between the DF and the State of Mexico, low-height cloud layers were presented.
Selected routes:
