This was the work of the cale<0xC3><0xB1>o who identified the body of Alfonso Cano
A Cali lofoscopicist went down in history as the man who confirmed the death of "Alfonso Cano".
The work of these officials is key.
On November 4th, a lofoscopicist from the CTI of Cali went down in history as the man who confirmed the identity of the top FARC leader: "Alfonso Cano", through the intersection of his fingerprints.
Of the seven lophoscopics who work in the CTI sectional, that week was Eliazar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez, a man from Puerto Tejada who has been working in the area of judicial investigation for 21 years.
At the beginning of his career, Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez worked in Choc<0xC3><0xB3> municipalities, where he often had to be interned for more than five days in the jungle to reach the site where the corpses were to be identified.
In 2000 he moved to the capital of the Valley and, after taking the corresponding courses, specialized in lophoscopy, which is the study of the skin of friction, that is, of the palms of the hands and feet.
The week of the operation against alias Alfonso Cano, Eliazar was warned to wear minimal clothing for three days.
Something big was waiting for him.
On Friday night he left for the Cauca in a helicopter from Palmyra.
He knew that he had to identify two bodies and that one of them was suspected to be from the man who was leading the world's oldest guerrilla, so he was asked to carry the decadactile card of William Leon Saenz (his real name).
However, when he arrived with the research team at the site where the body was located, he did not recognize it by its physical appearance, as it was very different from what he had seen in the media.
He was beardless, dressed like a peasant in the area, without glasses and much thinner.
But the footprints don't lie.
Accompanied by a Galtonian magnifying glass, ink, a transplanter and a flashlight, Eliazar compared the fingerprints of the corpse to those of the card.
His eye did not fail him: it was "Alfonso Cano".
That same night, the man from Puerto Tejada was in charge of confirming to the Minister of Defense, Juan Carlos Pinz<0xC3><0xB3>n, that he was the chief of the FARC.
In Search of the Footprint
For a typist from the Sij<0xC3><0xAD>n de Cali, the recognition that President Juan Manuel Santos made to Eliazar Gonz<0xC3><0xA1>lez, at the press conference for the operation against "Cano", is very significant.
Many people do not know our work.
Dactyloscopy is an exact science, with no margin for error, that can become key in solving crimes.
Apart from the identification of bodies, lophoscopicists support investigations into crimes such as theft and murder and confirm the identity of the captured persons.
When caught, many criminals present false cards or have no papers.
We take their fingerprints and look for them in the database.
The investigator said that, in a case of theft, it was up to him to remove a piece of a wall from a house, because in that place the thief had supported his hand to take out a safe full of jewelry and money.
“The walls are difficult because they are not suitable surfaces to take out a fingerprint, but in that case we were able to get the fingerprint from all over the hand and identify the offender, who had participated in different thefts,” he recalled.
Footprints can also discard or reassert suspects in homicide cases.
They recently found a dead man, with bottles of liquor around him.
The investigation determined that a family member could be a suspect in the crime and, indeed, a footprint on the bottle coincided.
Although this does not guarantee that he was the murderer, it does place him at the scene of the crime.
A CTI typist explained that on the objects “the footprints are taken out with chemical or physical reagents.”
When they appear, a transplanter or tape is used to lift them.
After this, the prints are sent to the Asif, which is the criminal database, or to the Registry.
“The problem is that there are still many undocumented Colombians,” the ITC expert said.
He clarified that not everything is as shown on the CSI television show.
Just as not everything that shines is gold, not everything that is touched becomes a footprint.
However, if it can be used, if the respective match is made.
