“I was very happy for Eden, for his progress and for being Belgian.”
"I want to move forward," says the Lille forward.
As for the contrast between his presentations in his team and in the selection, "it is a set", it has been justified.
“I’m in Lille all year round, which doesn’t apply to Belgium.
“I have to sit down.”
Called to play against Romania on Friday night, given this match against France, Hazard comes to Saint-Denis to finally "glow".
Don’t forget about “pleasure”.
He has been encouraging the Blues since he was seven, as well as during the winning campaigns of 1998 and 2000.
“I’ve always been a fan,” he says.
Certainly, that will especially reinforce the "particular" character of the meeting.
Especially because he will face "Mathieu (Debuchy), Yohan (Cabaye) and Adil (Rami)," he recalls.
“We just faced each other recently.
"Playing against them is always a joy."
With simplicity, Leekens has made reference to "pride".
"Pride" for playing "a gala game".
"Pride" also to check, as a "neighbor", that France "returns to be a very high-level team", about a year after Knysna's trauma.
“Laurent Blanc has done a formidable job,” he said enthusiastically.
While Belgium will not attend the next European competition, the coach would be delighted to be able to share a plane with the Bleus to... Brazil, in 2014.
“Our little Belgians are growing,” he said.
“We’re building something; the players are ambitious, they’re hungry.
"You'll be able to see him in the next matches." Including the match against France.
